    • Method Detail

      • getAssigneeNode

        public Identifier getAssigneeNode()
        Get the node that is having its value modified. In other words, the left hand value of the equation. For instance, in the statement: "int j = 35" int j is the left hand value of the equation.
        Returns:
        The node that represents the variable that is being assigned.

      • getAssignment

        public Value getAssignment()
        Get the node that is being used to set the value of the assignee node. In other words, the right hand value of the equation. For instance, in the statement: "int j = 35" 35 is the right hand value of the equation.
        Returns:
        The node that represents the value that the assignee variable is being assigned to.

      • decodeStatement

        public static Assignment decodeStatement(Node parent,
                         java.lang.String statement,
                         Location location,
                         boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into an Assignment if possible. If it is not possible, then null is returned.

        Example inputs include:
        • int variableName = 45
        • personsName = "Bob"
        • Person myPeep = new Person(54)
        • area = width * height / 2
        • int newSize = array.getSize() + 5
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to decode into an Assignment.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The new Assignment if it decodes properly. If not, it returns null.

      • decodeStatement

        public static Assignment decodeStatement(Node parent,
                         java.lang.String statement,
                         Location location,
                         boolean require,
                         boolean addDeclaration)
        Decode the given statement into an Assignment if possible. If it is not possible, then null is returned.

        Example inputs include:
        • int variableName = 45
        • personsName = "Bob"
        • Person myPeep = new Person(54)
        • area = width * height / 2
        • int newSize = array.getSize() + 5
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to decode into an Assignment.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        addDeclaration - Whether or not to add the declaration to the nearest scope, if the left hand value of the equation is a variable declaration.
        Returns:
        The new Assignment if it decodes properly. If not, it returns null.

      • decodeRightHandSide

        public static Node decodeRightHandSide(Node parent,
                       java.lang.String rhs,
                       Location location,
                       boolean require)
        Decode the right hand side of an assignment into an Node if possible. If it is not possible, then null is returned. The right hand side of an assignment must represent a value.

        Example inputs include:
        • 45
        • "Bob"
        • new Person(54)
        • width * height / 2
        • array.getSize() + 5
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        rhs - The right hand side to decode into an Assignment.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The new Node if it decodes properly. If not, it returns null.
